+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **POGLS V3.4 → V3.5**                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| Upgrade Summary · WAL + Compute Stack                                 |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**► Throughput Comparison**

  ------------------------------ ------------- ---------------- ----------
  **Metric**                     **V3.4        **V3.5 After**   **Gain**
                                 Before**                       

  fdatasync / write (1 op)       \~200 ops/s   **---**          **---**

  Group commit batch 256         \~47k ops/s   **---**          **---**

  Group commit batch 1024        ---           **\~460k ops/s** **10×**

  mmap + MS_SYNC (1024)          ---           **\~370k ops/s** **8×**

  mmap + MS_ASYNC (4 stripes)    ---           **\~13.6M        **65k×**
                                               ops/s**          

  Compute pipeline (memory)      \~400M ops/s  **\~490M ops/s** **1.2×**

  L0Ring push/pop                ---           **\~140M ops/s** **new**

  clut_pipeline (3 LUT ops)      \~3-5 ns      **\~2.2 ns**     **2×**
  ------------------------------ ------------- ---------------- ----------

**► Pipeline Architecture (V3.5)**

  --------------------- ------------------------------------- ----------------
  **Layer**             **Description**                       **Latency**

  **Compute Engine**    Rubik · Morton · Bitboard · Frontier  \~2 ns

  **ComputeLUT**        10KB L1-packed clut_pipeline()        \~2 ns

  **L0Ring**            65536 × 32B = 2MB MPSC lock-free      \~7 ns

  **CommitWorker**      background thread pop_batch(1024)     \~30 ns/batch

  **WALStripeRouter**   lsn & 3 → 4 parallel WAL files        1 bit op

  **WALMmap × 4**       mmap + MS_ASYNC zero-copy append      \~5 ns

  **Flusher × 4**       background msync non-blocking         async

  **NVMe**              kernel page flush parallel queues     \~0.3 ms
  --------------------- ------------------------------------- ----------------

**► Files Changed / Added (V3.4 core untouched)**

  ------------------------------ --------------------------------------------
  **File**                       **What changed / added**

  pogls_wal_stripe.h **\[MOD\]** WSRecord 28B → 32B + \_Static_assert guards

  pogls_exec_window.h            EWRecord 32B, EW_MAX_OPS 256→1024,
  **\[MOD\]**                    WAL_BATCH_BYTES alias

  pogls_wal_mmap.h/.c            mmap WAL: fallocate 8GB, MS_SYNC/ASYNC,
  **\[NEW\]**                    wal_alloc_record()

  pogls_compute_lut.h/.c         ComputeLUT 10KB L1-packed:
  **\[NEW\]**                    Rubik+Morton+NodeLUT

  pogls_wal_l0_ring.h            L0Ring 65536 slots, SPSC+MPSC, pop_batch
  **\[NEW\]**                    1024

  pogls_exec_window_lf.h         ExecWindowLF: CAS ring, ewlf_push/pop_batch
  **\[NEW\]**                    

  pogls_wal_stripe_router.h/.c   WALStripeRouter: 4 stripes, lsn&3 routing,
  **\[NEW\]**                    parallel NVMe

  pogls_wal_commit_worker.h/.c   CommitWorker thread: L0→EW→Router loop
  **\[NEW\]**                    

  pogls_frontier.h **\[NEW\]**   pogls_frontier_diffuse() + global
                                 node_adj_map\[\]

  pogls_bitboard.h **\[MOD\]**   bitboard_set(), bitboard_next_active()
                                 team-B compat

  pogls_rubik.h **\[MOD\]**      pogls_rubik_move/inverse/parity() aliases,
                                 dedup

  pogls_morton.h **\[MOD\]**     pogls_morton_encode(), \_pogls_expand_bits()
                                 aliases

  pogls_compute_stack.c          node_adj_map\[\], frontier_build_adj_map(),
  **\[MOD\]**                    cross-assert

  pogls_bench_colab.c            Standalone single-file benchmark (this
  **\[NEW\]**                    session)
